    <text>
        <body>

            <div type="page" xml:id="pg_027">


                <div type="panelGrp" xml:id="eg_0001">


                    <cbml:panel n="1" characters="#dennis #father">

                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#father"> I know! I'll <emph rendition="#b"
                                >MAKE</emph> you a pair of skis! </cbml:balloon>
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#dennis"> Aw, Dad! </cbml:balloon>
                        <note type="panelDesc"> Dennis' father is shown walking, smoking a pipe, as
                            Dennis trails behind him. </note>
                    </cbml:panel>


                    <cbml:panel n="2" characters="#dennis #father">
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#dennis"> How 'bout that <emph
                                rendition="#b">KITE</emph> ya made me, an'it wouldn't <emph
                                rendition="#b">FLY</emph>? An' that <emph rendition="#b">BOAT</emph>
                            ya made me an'it <emph rendition="#b">SANK</emph>? An' that..... </cbml:balloon>
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#father"> Okay, Okay!</cbml:balloon>
                        <note type="panelDesc"> Dennis trails behind his father with his arms spread
                            outward in exclamation, Dennis' father wears a frown while smoking his
                            pipe.</note>
                    </cbml:panel>


                    <cbml:panel n="3" characters="#dennis #father">
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#father">
                            <emph rendition="#b"> THESE</emph> skis are practically ready made! </cbml:balloon>
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#dennis"> They are? </cbml:balloon>
                        <note type="panelDesc"> Dennis' father breaks off two planks of wood from a
                            barrel full of trash, Dennis wears a suprised and confused face.</note>
                    </cbml:panel>




                    <cbml:panel n="4" characters="#dennis #father">
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="father"> Uh-huh! I'll just nail this piece
                            of innertube on...bend the nails under...and... </cbml:balloon>
                        <note type="panelDesc"> Dennis observes his father in the shed as he nails
                            the piece of innertube onto one of the planks of wood. </note>
                    </cbml:panel>




                    <cbml:panel n="5" characters="#dennis #father">
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#father"> And there you are! A pair of
                            skis! </cbml:balloon>
                        <cbml:balloon rendition="#jaggies" type="speech" who="#dennis"> Hey! Pretty
                            keen! Make a pair for Tommy, too, huh? </cbml:balloon>
                        <note type="panelDesc"> Dennis' father presents him with the finished skis
                            made from wood planks. </note>
                    </cbml:panel>


                    <cbml:panel n="6" characters="#dennis #father">
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#father"> Well, that's mighty generous of
                            you to give Tommy a pair. </cbml:balloon>
                        <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#dennis">
                            <emph rendition="#b"> GIVE</emph> 'em? I'm gonna <emph rendition="#b">
                                SELL</emph> 'em to him!</cbml:balloon>
                        <note type="panelDesc"> Dennis' father is shown holding a hammer, working on
                            a new pair of skis for Tommy. Dennis holds his own newly made pair.
                        </note>
                    </cbml:panel>


                </div>
                <pb/>
            </div>
